  [36m           FIELD 3:    Load Case Number[39m
  
  [36m      RECORD 8:[39m
  [36m           FIELD 1: Eigenvalue[39m
  
  [36m      RECORD 9:      Format (I10)[39m
  [36m           FIELD 1:          Node Number[39m
  
  [36m      RECORD 10:     Format (6E13.5)[39m
  [36m           FIELDS 1-N:       Data At This Node (NDV Real Or[39m
  [36m                     Complex Values)[39m
  
  [36m      Records 9 And 10 Are Repeated For Each Node.[39m
  
  [36m      Notes:[39m
  [36m      1        Id Lines May Not Be Blank.  If No Information Is[39m
  [36m                  Required, The Word [32m"[32mNone[32m"[36m Must Appear  Columns 1-4.[39m
  
  [36m      2        For Complex Data There Will Be 2*Ndv Data Items At Each[39m
  [36m                  Node. The Order Is Real Part For Value 1,  Imaginary[39m
  [36m                  Part For Value 1, Etc.[39m
  [36m      3        The Order Of Values For Various Data  Characteristics[39m
  [36m                  Is:[39m
  [36m                      3 DOF Global Vector:[39m
  [36m                              X, Y, Z[39m
  
  [36m                      6 DOF Global Vector:[39m
  [36m                              X, Y, Z,[39m
  [36m                              Rx, Ry, Rz[39m
  
  [36m                      Symmetric Global Tensor:[39m
  [36m                              Sxx, Sxy, Syy,[39m
  [36m                              Sxz, Syz, Szz[39m
  
  [36m                      General Global Tensor:[39m
  [36m                              Sxx, Syx, Szx,[39m
  [36m                              Sxy, Syy, Szy,[39m
  [36m                              Sxz, Syz, Szz[39m
  
  [36m                      Shell And Plate Element Load:[39m
  [36m                              Fx, Fy, Fxy,[39m
  [36m                              Mx, My, Mxy,[39m
  [36m                              Vx, Vy[39m
  
  [36m      4        Id Line 1 Always Appears On Plots In Output Display.[39m
  [36m      5        If Specific Data Type Is [32m"[32mUnknown,[32m"[36m ID Line 2 Is[39m
  [36m                  Displayed As Data Type In Output Display.[39m
  [36m      6        Typical Fortran I/O Statements For The Data Sections[39m
  [36m                  Are:[39m
  
  [36m                               Read(Lun,1000)Num[39m
  [36m                               Write[39m
  [36m                      1000 Format (I10)[39m
  [36m                               Read(Lun,1010) (VAL(I),I=1,NDV)[39m
  [36m                               Write[39m
  [36m                      1010 format (6e13.5)[39m
  
  [36m                      Where:     Num Is Node Number[39m
  [36m                                 Val Is Real Or Complex Data  Array[39m
  [36m                                 Ndv Is Number Of Data Values  Per Node[39m
  
  [36m      7         Data Characteristic Values Imply The Following Values[39m
  [36m                  Of Ndv:[39m
  [36m                    Scalar: 1[39m
  [36m                    3 DOF Global Vector: 3[39m
  [36m                    6 DOF Global Vector: 6[39m
  [36m                    Symmetric Global Tensor: 6[39m
  [36m                    General Global Tensor: 9[39m
  
  [36m      8        Data Associated With I-DEAS Test Has The Following[39m
  [36m                  Special Forms of Specific Data Type and ID Line 5.[39m
  
  [36m               For Record 6 Field 4-Specific Data Type, values 0[39m
  [36m               through 12 are as defined above.  13 and 15 through 19 are:[39m
  
  [36m                           13: excitation force[39m
  [36m                           15: pressure[39m
  [36m                           16: mass[39m
  [36m                           17: time[39m
  [36m                           18: frequency[39m
  [36m                           19: rpm[39m
  
  [36m               The form of ID Line 5 is:[39m
  
  [36m               Format (4I10)[39m
  [36m               FIELD 1:  Reference Coordinate Label[39m
  
  [36m               FIELD 2:  Reference Coordinate Direction[39m
  [36m                            1: X Direction[39m
  [36m                           -1: -X Direction[39m
  [36m                            2: Y Direction[39m
  [36m                           -2: -Y Direction[39m
  [36m                            3: Z Direction[39m
  [36m                           -3: -Z Direction[39m
  
  [36m               FIELD 3:  Numerator Signal Code[39m
  [36m                            see Specific Data Type above[39m
  
  [36m               FIELD 4:  Denominator Signal Code[39m
  [36m                            see Specific Data Type above[39m
  
  
  [36m               Also note that the modal mass in record 8 is calculated[39m
  [36m               from the parameter table by I-DEAS Test.[39m
  
  [36m      9        Any Record With All 0.0's Data Entries Need Not (But[39m
  [36m                  May) Appear.[39m
  
  [36m      10       A Direct Result Of 9 Is That If No Records 9 And 10[39m
  [36m                  Appear, All Data For The Data Set Is 0.0.[39m
  
  [36m      11       When New Analysis Types Are Added, Record 7 Fields 1[39m
  [36m                  And 2 Are Always > Or = 1 With Dummy Integer And[39m
  [36m                  Real Zero Data If Data Is Not Required. If Complex[39m
  [36m                  Data Is Needed, It Is Treated As Two Real Numbers,[39m
  [36m                  Real Part Followed By Imaginary Point.[39m
  
  [36m      12       Dataloaders Use The Following ID Line Convention:[39m
  [36m                          1.   (80A1) Model[39m
  [36m                              Identification[39m
  [36m                          2.   (80A1) Run[39m
  [36m                              Identification[39m
  [36m                          3.   (80A1) Run[39m
  [36m                              Date/Time[39m
  [36m                          4.   (80A1) Load Case[39m
  [36m                              Name[39m
  
  [36m                      For Static:[39m
  [36m                          5.   (17h Load Case[39m
  [36m                              Number;, I10) For[39m
  [36m                              Normal Mode:[39m
  [36m                          5.   (10h Mode Same,[39m
  [36m                              I10, 10H Frequency,[39m
  [36m                              E13.5)[39m
  [36m      13       No Maximum Value For Ndv .[39m
  
  [36m      14       Typical Fortran I/O Statements For Processing Records 7[39m
  [36m                  And 8.[39m
  
  [36m                        Read (LUN,1000)NINT,NRVAL,(IPAR(I),I=1,NINT[39m
  [36m                   1000 Format (8I10)[39m
  [36m                        Read (Lun,1010) (RPAV(I),I=1,NRVAL)[39m
  [36m                   1010 Format (6E13.5)[39m
  
  [36m      15       For Situations With Reduced [90m# Dof's, Use 3 DOF[39m
  [36m                  Translations Or 6 DOF Translation And Rotation With[39m
  [36m                  Unused Values = 0.[39m

                               Read(Lun,1000)Num

                               Write
                      1010 format (6e13.5)

                                 Val Is Real Or Complex Data  Array

                    Scalar: 1
                    3 DOF Global Vector: 3
                    6 DOF Global Vector: 6
                    Symmetric Global Tensor: 6
                    General Global Tensor: 9

      8        Data Associated With I-DEAS Test Has The Following
                  Special Forms of Specific Data Type and ID Line 5.

               For Record 6 Field 4-Specific Data Type, values 0
               through 12 are as defined above.  13 and 15 through 19 are:

                           13: excitation force
                           15: pressure
                           16: mass
                           17: time
                           18: frequency
                           19: rpm

               Format (4I10)
               FIELD 1:  Reference Coordinate Label

                            1: X Direction
                           -1: -X Direction
                            2: Y Direction
                           -2: -Y Direction
                            3: Z Direction
                           -3: -Z Direction

               FIELD 3:  Numerator Signal Code
                            see Specific Data Type above

               FIELD 4:  Denominator Signal Code
                            see Specific Data Type above


               Also note that the modal mass in record 8 is calculated
               from the parameter table by I-DEAS Test.

      9        Any Record With All 0.0's Data Entries Need Not (But
                  May) Appear.

      10       A Direct Result Of 9 Is That If No Records 9 And 10
                  Appear, All Data For The Data Set Is 0.0.

      11       When New Analysis Types Are Added, Record 7 Fields 1
                  And 2 Are Always > Or = 1 With Dummy Integer And
                  Real Zero Data If Data Is Not Required. If Complex
                  Data Is Needed, It Is Treated As Two Real Numbers,
                  Real Part Followed By Imaginary Point.

      12       Dataloaders Use The Following ID Line Convention:
                          1.   (80A1) Model
                              Identification
                          2.   (80A1) Run
                              Identification
                          3.   (80A1) Run
                              Date/Time
                          4.   (80A1) Load Case
                              Name

                      For Static:
                          5.   (17h Load Case
                              Number;, I10) For
                              Normal Mode:
                          5.   (10h Mode Same,
                              I10, 10H Frequency,
                              E13.5)
      13       No Maximum Value For Ndv .

      14       Typical Fortran I/O Statements For Processing Records 7

                        Read (LUN,1000)NINT,NRVAL,(IPAR(I),I=1,NINT

                        Read (Lun,1010) (RPAV(I),I=1,NRVAL)
                   1010 Format (6E13.5)

      15       For Situations With Reduced # Dof's, Use 3 DOF

           FIELD 3:    Real Part Of Modal A
           FIELD 4:    Imaginary Part Of Modal A
           FIELD 5:    Real Part Of Modal B
           FIELD 6:    Imaginary Part Of Modal B

      For Analysis Type = 4, Transient

      RECORD 7:
           FIELD 1:    2
           FIELD 2:    1
           FIELD 3:    Load Case Number
           FIELD 4:    Time Step Number

      RECORD 8:
           FIELD 1: Time (Seconds)

      For Analysis Type = 5, Frequency Response

      RECORD 7:
           FIELD 1:    2
           FIELD 2:    1
           FIELD 3:    Load Case Number
           FIELD 4:    Frequency Step Number

      RECORD 8:
           FIELD 1:    Frequency (Hertz)

      For Analysis Type = 6, Buckling

      RECORD 7:
           FIELD 1:    1
           FIELD 2:    1
           FIELD 3:    Load Case Number

      RECORD 8:
           FIELD 1: Eigenvalue

      RECORD 9:      Format (I10)
           FIELD 1:          Node Number

      RECORD 10:     Format (6E13.5)
           FIELDS 1-N:       Data At This Node (NDV Real Or
                     Complex Values)

      Records 9 And 10 Are Repeated For Each Node.

      Notes:
      1        Id Lines May Not Be Blank.  If No Information Is
                  Required, The Word "None" Must Appear  Columns 1-4.

      2        For Complex Data There Will Be 2*Ndv Data Items At Each
                  Node. The Order Is Real Part For Value 1,  Imaginary
                  Part For Value 1, Etc.
      3        The Order Of Values For Various Data  Characteristics
                  Is:
                      3 DOF Global Vector:
                              X, Y, Z

                      6 DOF Global Vector:
                              X, Y, Z,
                              Rx, Ry, Rz

                      Symmetric Global Tensor:
                              Sxx, Sxy, Syy,
                              Sxz, Syz, Szz

                      General Global Tensor:
                              Sxx, Syx, Szx,
                              Sxy, Syy, Szy,
                              Sxz, Syz, Szz

                      Shell And Plate Element Load:
                              Fx, Fy, Fxy,
                              Mx, My, Mxy,
                              Vx, Vy

      4        Id Line 1 Always Appears On Plots In Output Display.
      5        If Specific Data Type Is "Unknown," ID Line 2 Is
                  Displayed As Data Type In Output Display.
      6        Typical Fortran I/O Statements For The Data Sections
                  Are:

                               Read(Lun,1000)Num
                               Write
                      1000 Format (I10)
                               Read(Lun,1010) (VAL(I),I=1,NDV)
                               Write
                      1010 format (6e13.5)

                      Where:     Num Is Node Number
                                 Val Is Real Or Complex Data  Array
                                 Ndv Is Number Of Data Values  Per Node

      7         Data Characteristic Values Imply The Following Values
                  Of Ndv:
                    Scalar: 1
                    3 DOF Global Vector: 3
                    6 DOF Global Vector: 6
                    Symmetric Global Tensor: 6
                    General Global Tensor: 9

      8        Data Associated With I-DEAS Test Has The Following
                  Special Forms of Specific Data Type and ID Line 5.

               For Record 6 Field 4-Specific Data Type, values 0
               through 12 are as defined above.  13 and 15 through 19 are:

                           13: excitation force
                           15: pressure
                           16: mass
                           17: time
                           18: frequency
                           19: rpm

               The form of ID Line 5 is:

               Format (4I10)
               FIELD 1:  Reference Coordinate Label

               FIELD 2:  Reference Coordinate Direction
                            1: X Direction
                           -1: -X Direction
                            2: Y Direction
                           -2: -Y Direction
                            3: Z Direction
                           -3: -Z Direction

               FIELD 3:  Numerator Signal Code
                            see Specific Data Type above

               FIELD 4:  Denominator Signal Code
                            see Specific Data Type above


               Also note that the modal mass in record 8 is calculated
               from the parameter table by I-DEAS Test.

      9        Any Record With All 0.0's Data Entries Need Not (But
                  May) Appear.

      10       A Direct Result Of 9 Is That If No Records 9 And 10
                  Appear, All Data For The Data Set Is 0.0.

      11       When New Analysis Types Are Added, Record 7 Fields 1
                  And 2 Are Always > Or = 1 With Dummy Integer And
                  Real Zero Data If Data Is Not Required. If Complex
                  Data Is Needed, It Is Treated As Two Real Numbers,
                  Real Part Followed By Imaginary Point.

      12       Dataloaders Use The Following ID Line Convention:
                          1.   (80A1) Model
                              Identification
                          2.   (80A1) Run
                              Identification
                          3.   (80A1) Run
                              Date/Time
                          4.   (80A1) Load Case
                              Name

                      For Static:
                          5.   (17h Load Case
                              Number;, I10) For
                              Normal Mode:
                          5.   (10h Mode Same,
                              I10, 10H Frequency,
                              E13.5)
      13       No Maximum Value For Ndv .

      14       Typical Fortran I/O Statements For Processing Records 7
                  And 8.

                        Read (LUN,1000)NINT,NRVAL,(IPAR(I),I=1,NINT
                   1000 Format (8I10)
                        Read (Lun,1010) (RPAV(I),I=1,NRVAL)
                   1010 Format (6E13.5)

      15       For Situations With Reduced # Dof's, Use 3 DOF
                  Translations Or 6 DOF Translation And Rotation With
                  Unused Values = 0.
